         <abstract>
            <p>
               The Maṣḥafa krǝstǝnnā is the service book for the administration of the Sacraments of Christian Initiation. It includes the preparatory rites and the threefold sercive
               of baptism, chrism and Eucharist. Its structure is the same as of the baptismal book of the Coptic Church.
            </p>
              <p> It is sometimes grouped in manuscripts with <title ref="LIT1975Mashaf"/>. 
            </p>
            <p>The short version agrees with the long version <title ref="LIT3949MashafaKrL"/> until the recitation of the Credo, then there are many prayers missing, 
               however, the Psalms<title ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps61"> 61</title> and <title ref="LIT2000Mazmur#Ps113">113, 20-end</title> are absent from the Latin translations.
               The ṣawātǝw prayers are less elaborated than in the Latin translations, here there are only the prayers "pro pace", "pro pontifice", "pro congregatione" and "pro Catechumenis".</p>
